---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import RelatedLinks from '../../components/RelatedLinks.astro';
import { url } from '../../lib/site';
---

<Layout
  title="Try a Demo Activity"
  description="A non-diagnostic, hands-on demo of the Sight Scout activity style. Fixed comfortable sizes, no scoring, no data collected. Not a vision test."
>
  <h1>Try the activity style: a demo for grown-ups.</h1>

  <div class="mt-10">
    <!-- Intro / gate screen (SPEC.md §6.2) -->
    <section id="screen-intro" class="card max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-ink/90">
        This is a hands-on demonstration of how Sight Scout's activity <em>feels</em>: the
        shape-matching, the pacing, the encouragement. It is <strong>not</strong> a vision test.
        It uses fixed, comfortable shape sizes, adapts to nothing, measures nothing, and stores
        nothing. Please don't use it to check anyone's eyesight. That job belongs to a
        comprehensive exam by an eye care professional.
      </p>
      <button id="demo-start-btn" type="button" class="btn btn-primary mt-6" data-autofocus>
        Got it, show me
      </button>
    </section>

    <!-- Optional calibration vignette (SPEC.md §6.3) -->
    <section id="screen-calibration" class="card max-w-2xl" hidden>
      <h2 class="text-lg">Match me to a bank card</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/70">
        In the real app, this is step one. It's how shapes get exactly the right physical size
        on any device.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-col items-center gap-4">
        <div
          id="cal-card"
          class="h-24 rounded-lg border-2 border-dashed border-teal bg-sky"
          style="width: 200px;"
          aria-hidden="true"
        ></div>
        <label for="cal-slider" class="text-sm font-semibold">
          Drag to match the width of a real bank card held against your screen
        </label>
        <input id="cal-slider" type="range" min="90" max="380" value="200" step="1" class="w-full max-w-xs" />
        <p id="cal-readout" class="font-mono text-sm text-ink/70" aria-live="polite"></p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <button id="cal-confirm-btn" type="button" class="btn btn-primary">Looks right</button>
        <button id="cal-skip-btn" type="button" class="btn btn-secondary">Skip and play</button>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Activity screen (SPEC.md §6.4) -->
    <section id="screen-activity" class="max-w-2xl" hidden>
      <p class="inline-block rounded-full bg-coral/15 px-4 py-1 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-coral">
        Demo, not a vision test
      </p>

      <p id="round-indicator" class="mt-4 text-sm font-semibold text-ink/60" aria-live="polite"></p>
      <h2 class="mt-1 text-xl">Which way does the ring open?</h2>

      <div class="mt-8 flex items-center justify-center gap-6">
        <svg
          class="leaf-flanker hidden sm:block"
          viewBox="0 0 40 60" width="40" height="60" aria-hidden="true"
        >
          <path d="M20 5 C34 20, 34 45, 20 55 C6 45, 6 20, 20 5 Z" fill="var(--color-leaf)" opacity="0.7" />
        </svg>

        <div class="flex h-44 w-44 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-white shadow-inner">
          <svg id="ring-svg" data-autofocus tabindex="-1" role="img" aria-label="A ring shape with a gap on one side">
            <path fill="none" stroke="var(--color-ink)" stroke-linecap="round" />
          </svg>
        </div>

        <svg
          class="leaf-flanker hidden sm:block"
          viewBox="0 0 40 60" width="40" height="60" aria-hidden="true"
        >
          <path d="M20 5 C34 20, 34 45, 20 55 C6 45, 6 20, 20 5 Z" fill="var(--color-leaf)" opacity="0.7" />
        </svg>
      </div>

      <div class="mx-auto mt-8 grid w-fit grid-cols-3 grid-rows-3 gap-2">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary col-start-2 row-start-1 !min-h-16 !min-w-16" data-direction="up" aria-label="Up">
          <span aria-hidden="true">↑</span>
        </button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary col-start-1 row-start-2 !min-h-16 !min-w-16" data-direction="left" aria-label="Left">
          <span aria-hidden="true">←</span>
        </button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary col-start-3 row-start-2 !min-h-16 !min-w-16" data-direction="right" aria-label="Right">
          <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary col-start-2 row-start-3 !min-h-16 !min-w-16" data-direction="down" aria-label="Down">
          <span aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-center text-xs text-ink/50">Tip: arrow keys work too.</p>

      <p id="feedback-message" class="mt-6 min-h-8 text-center text-lg font-semibold text-teal-dark" aria-live="polite"></p>

      <div class="mt-4 flex justify-center">
        <button id="continue-btn" type="button" class="btn btn-primary" hidden>Next ring</button>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- "Aha" interstitial (SPEC.md §6.5) -->
    <section id="screen-aha" class="card max-w-2xl" hidden>
      <p class="text-ink/90">
        In the real app, the sizes would now be adapting to the player. Two right answers make
        the next ring a bit smaller; a miss makes it bigger. That "staircase" is how a handful
        of playful rounds can home in on the just-tricky-enough zone.
      </p>
      <a href={`${url('science/')}#the-adaptive-staircase`} class="mt-3 inline-block font-semibold">See the math</a>
      <div class="mt-6">
        <button id="aha-continue-btn" type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-autofocus>Continue</button>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- End screen (SPEC.md §6.6) -->
    <section id="screen-end" class="card max-w-2xl" hidden>
      <h2 class="text-xl">That's the feel of it.</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-ink/90">
        You've seen the shape-matching, the pacing, and the encouragement. In Sight Scout
        itself, each eye takes its own turn (pirate patch and all), sizes adapt using the
        staircase math, and parents get plain-language observations afterward.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-ink/90">
        <strong>One reminder:</strong> this demo measured nothing, and Sight Scout itself
        doesn't diagnose anything. For real answers about a child's vision, see an eye care
        professional.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href={url('how-it-works/')} class="btn btn-primary" data-autofocus>How the full activity works</a>
        <button id="play-again-btn" type="button" class="btn btn-secondary">Play the demo again</button>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <RelatedLinks
    links={[
      { href: 'how-it-works/', label: 'How the full activity works', desc: 'Calibration, the pirate patch, and the trail notes.' },
      { href: 'science/', label: 'The science and math', desc: 'Why sizes, distances, and staircases matter.' },
      { href: 'faq/', label: 'FAQ', desc: 'Including what this demo does and does not do.' },
    ]}
  />

  <script>
    import { initDemo } from '../../scripts/demo';
    initDemo();
  </script>
</Layout>
